## Historical Photographs and Content

The MIT License above applies ONLY to the source code, software, and technical
implementation of this project (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and project structure).

Historical photographs and images displayed in this application may be subject
to separate copyright restrictions and are NOT covered by the MIT License.

### Image Rights and Usage

- Historical photographs may be protected by copyright held by their original
  creators, archives, libraries, or other rights holders.

- Many photographs in this project are sourced from or inspired by collections at:
  - [St. Louis Public Library](https://www.slpl.org/)
  - [Missouri Historical Society](https://mohistory.org/)

- These institutions maintain their own copyright policies, usage restrictions,
  and licensing requirements for their historical photograph collections.

- Users of this software are responsible for obtaining proper permissions and
  licenses before using, reproducing, or distributing any historical images.

- The inclusion of images in this repository or application does not imply
  that they are in the public domain or freely licensed.

- Image metadata in `src/data/locations.json` is provided for reference purposes
  only and should be verified for accuracy and rights status.

### Recommended Practice

When using this software with historical photographs:

1. Verify the copyright status of each image
2. Obtain necessary permissions from rights holders
3. Provide proper attribution as required
4. Replace placeholder images with properly licensed content
5. Document image sources and permissions in your deployment

For questions about specific image rights, please contact the relevant archives,
libraries, or copyright holders directly.
